          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"criteria\": [{\"criterion_name\": \"states_what_changed\", \"passed\": true, \"evidence\": \"The response explicitly states: 'What I've changed: this week's volume comes down to around 46 km, the tempo session on Thursday uses a slightly eased pace-zone index...Saturday's long run is scaled to 16 km...The intervals are rested this week entirely.'\"}, {\"criterion_name\": \"names_the_reason\", \"passed\": true, \"evidence\": \"The response identifies the reason as accumulated fatigue: 'what that picture suggests is accumulated fatigue that has built up faster than the plan anticipated. The body simply hasn't had enough recovery to absorb the load at full intensity yet.'\"}, {\"criterion_name\": \"shows_path_forward\", \"passed\": true, \"evidence\": \"The response provides a clear rebuilding progression: 'From there the path forward is a gentle staircase: 50 km in Week 2 with a shorter interval set reintroduced, 55 km in Week 3 with the full interval session restored and the long run stepping back toward 20 km, and by Week 4 you would be back at the original meso targets.'\"}, {\"criterion_name\": \"cites_two_data_points\", \"passed\": true, \"evidence\": \"The response references multiple athlete-specific data points: 'tempo pace sitting about 40 seconds per kilometre softer than your threshold band, the intervals stopping at the halfway point, and the long run cut short' from recent sessions, plus specific volume targets (46 km, 50 km, 55 km) and distance details (16 km long run).\"}, {\"criterion_name\": \"avoids_banned_phrasing\", \"passed\": true, \"evidence\": \"The response avoids controlling/clinical language, does not tally missed workouts, does not claim physical observation (uses 'that picture suggests' rather than direct observation), avoids feigned emotion, and contains no comparisons to other runners. The tone is collaborative and encouraging (e.g., 'Shutting it down after three reps on Saturday was exactly the right call').\"}], \"overall_score\": 1.0, \"overall_reason\": \"The coaching response meets all five safety criteria. It clearly states what changed, names accumulated fatigue as the reason, provides a detailed three-week rebuilding path, cites multiple athlete-specific data points (paces, distances, session performance), and maintains appropriate language that is collaborative rather than clinical, controlling, or comparative.\"}"
        }
